# BDD 50 questions
bdd = [
("What is the Three Amigos ceremony?", "Meeting with Business (PO/BA), Developer, and Tester before implementing a user story. Review acceptance criteria, write Gherkin scenarios together, identify edge cases. Ensures shared understanding before coding starts. Typically 30-45 minutes per story. Output: approved feature file scenarios ready for automation.", "Collaboration process experience, not just definition."),
("What is living documentation?", "Feature files that serve as always-current documentation because they execute as tests. When code changes, scenarios fail until updated — keeping docs synced with behavior. Readable by non-technical stakeholders. Stored in git alongside code. More reliable than wiki pages that become stale.", "Docs that self-validate through test execution."),
("What is ubiquitous language?", "Shared vocabulary between business and tech teams used consistently in feature files, code, and conversations. If business says \"order\", Gherkin says \"order\", code uses Order class. Reduces miscommunication. Established during Three Amigos sessions. Documented in team glossary.", "Shared domain language across team boundaries."),
("What is Example Mapping?", "Workshop technique: index cards for Rules (yellow), Examples (green), Questions (red), Stories (blue). Map business rules to concrete examples before writing Gherkin. Identifies gaps and ambiguities early. 30-minute timeboxed session. Output feeds directly into feature file scenarios.", "Practical workshop facilitation experience."),
("What is Specification by Example?", "Define requirements as concrete examples rather than abstract statements. \"Login fails with wrong password\" not \"system validates credentials\". Examples become automated tests. Core BDD principle predating Cucumber. Ensures testable, unambiguous requirements.", "Concrete examples over vague requirements."),
("What is the difference between BDD and TDD?", "TDD: developer writes unit tests first, then code (Red-Green-Refactor). BDD: team defines behavior examples first using Gherkin, then automates. TDD focuses on code correctness at unit level. BDD focuses on behavior at feature level. Complementary — use both. BDD drives acceptance; TDD drives design.", "Complementary, not competing approaches."),
("What are common BDD anti-patterns?", "Imperative Gherkin (click, type, verify). Testing through UI only. No Three Amigos — QA writes Gherkin alone. Scenarios too long (20+ steps). Technical jargon in features. Treating BDD as just a testing tool. Duplicate step definitions. No living documentation mindset.", "Recognize and prevent anti-patterns from experience."),
("What is imperative vs declarative Gherkin?", "Imperative: \"When I click login and enter user and pass and click submit\". Declarative: \"When I login as admin\". Declarative hides implementation, survives UI changes. BDD best practice is declarative. Implementation details belong in step definitions and page objects only.", "Strong declarative preference with before/after examples."),
("What is the role of Product Owner in BDD?", "PO participates in Three Amigos, validates Gherkin scenarios match business intent, prioritizes scenarios for automation, reviews living documentation. PO doesn't write step definitions but approves feature file content. PO ensures scenarios cover acceptance criteria completely.", "PO as active BDD participant, not passive recipient."),
("How do you write good Gherkin scenarios?", "One behavior per scenario. Declarative language. Clear Given-When-Then. Meaningful scenario name. Relevant tags. Minimal Background. Use Scenario Outline for data variations. Max 10 steps. Readable by PO without technical explanation. Review in Three Amigos before automation.", "Quality Gherkin writing with team review process."),
("What is outside-in development?", "Start with user-facing acceptance scenarios (outside), then implement code (in) to make them pass. BDD enables this: write failing scenario first, implement feature, scenario passes. Ensures development driven by user value. Contrasts with inside-out (database up) approach.", "User-value-driven development approach."),
("How do you measure BDD ROI?", "Track: requirement defect reduction, time to onboard new team members (read feature files), regression test creation speed, PO confidence in releases. Compare defect escape rate before/after BDD. Measure scenario coverage vs acceptance criteria coverage. Qualitative: improved team communication.", "Quantifiable and qualitative BDD success metrics."),
("What is a Gherkin style guide?", "Team document defining: max steps per scenario, declarative language rules, naming conventions, tag strategy, when to use Background vs Given, Scenario Outline guidelines. Enforced in PR review. Example: \"Never use UI element names in Gherkin\". Prevents feature file quality drift.", "Team standards enforcement for Gherkin quality."),
("How do you handle BDD in Agile sprints?", "Three Amigos during refinement (sprint N-1). Scenarios written before development (sprint N). Automation during or after development. Demo using Gherkin scenarios in sprint review. Scenarios map to acceptance criteria on story. BDD scenarios are part of Definition of Done.", "BDD integrated into sprint ceremonies."),
("What is acceptance criteria vs BDD scenarios?", "Acceptance criteria: conditions on user story (often bullet points). BDD scenarios: executable Given-When-Then versions of those criteria. Each criterion maps to one or more scenarios. Scenarios are testable; criteria may be vague. Three Amigos converts criteria to scenarios.", "Criteria-to-scenario mapping process."),
("What is executable specification?", "Gherkin scenario that runs as automated test AND serves as specification. Single source of truth for behavior. Eliminates separate test plan documents. When application changes, failing scenario signals spec needs update. Core value proposition of BDD with Cucumber.", "Single artifact for spec and test."),
("What is domain-driven testing?", "Test organization mirrors business domain, not technical architecture. Feature files named by business capability: checkout.feature not test_page_3.feature. Steps use business language. Aligns testing with how stakeholders think about the product. Supports ubiquitous language principle.", "Business-domain-aligned test organization."),
("How do you do BDD for API testing?", "Feature files describe API behavior: \"When I create user with valid data Then response status is 201\". Same Gherkin principles — declarative, business-focused. Tag @api. No UI steps mixed in. API scenarios often faster and more stable than UI scenarios. Good BDD entry point for microservices.", "BDD beyond UI — API feature file examples."),
("How do you scale BDD across multiple teams?", "Shared Gherkin style guide and step library. Common glue package for reusable steps. Feature file ownership per team/product area. Central framework team maintains infrastructure. Regular cross-team sync on shared steps. Avoid duplicate step definitions across teams.", "Multi-team BDD governance experience."),
("What is BDD maturity model?", "Level 1: QA writes Gherkin alone. Level 2: Three Amigos for some stories. Level 3: All stories have Gherkin before development. Level 4: Living documentation trusted by stakeholders. Level 5: BDD drives product discovery. Assess team level and plan progression.", "Honest team maturity assessment and improvement plan."),
("What is feature file ownership?", "Each feature file owned by a team or feature area. PO approves content, QA automates, Dev reviews step definitions. Git CODEOWNERS for feature files. Changes require PO review. Prevents unauthorized scenario modifications. Clear ownership reduces orphaned scenarios.", "Ownership model preventing feature file chaos."),
("How do you handle legacy systems with BDD?", "Start with critical user journeys, not full coverage. Wrap legacy UI with page objects. Write scenarios for new features in BDD. Gradually add scenarios for legacy as areas are modified. Don't attempt big-bang BDD migration. Focus on highest business value flows first.", "Incremental BDD adoption for legacy systems."),
("What is incremental BDD adoption?", "Phase 1: Pilot one feature with Three Amigos. Phase 2: All new features use BDD. Phase 3: Retrofit critical existing flows. Phase 4: Full regression in BDD. Don't force entire team at once. Demonstrate value with pilot success. Provide training at each phase.", "Phased adoption plan with pilot-first approach."),
("What is BDD in regulated industries?", "Feature files serve as compliance evidence — auditable test records. Scenarios must trace to requirements (requirement ID in tag). Strict change control on feature files. Execution reports archived for audit. Gherkin provides readable evidence for non-technical auditors.", "Compliance and audit trail awareness."),
("What is non-automation BDD?", "Gherkin scenarios executed manually during exploratory or sprint testing. Not all scenarios need automation. Manual BDD scenarios guide structured exploratory testing. Automate high-value, repeatable scenarios. Manual for UX, visual, one-time investigations.", "BDD value beyond automation."),
("What is exploratory BDD?", "Use Gherkin structure to guide exploratory testing sessions. Tester deviates from script but documents findings in scenario format. Combines structured and exploratory approaches. Useful for new features where scenarios aren't fully known upfront.", "Flexible BDD application for discovery testing."),
("How do you facilitate a Three Amigos session?", "Timebox 30-45 min. Review story and acceptance criteria. Write Gherkin scenarios collaboratively. Identify questions (red cards in Example Mapping). Agree on scope. Assign automation owner. Document decisions. Don't let it become a design meeting — focus on behavior examples.", "Facilitation skills and session structure."),
("What is behavior coverage?", "Percentage of acceptance criteria covered by at least one Gherkin scenario. Unlike code coverage, measures business behavior testing completeness. Track: criteria count vs scenario count. Gap analysis: criteria without scenarios. Target: 100% criteria coverage for P1 features.", "Business behavior coverage metric."),
("How do you audit feature files?", "Quarterly review: obsolete scenarios, duplicated coverage, imperative Gherkin, missing tags, overly long scenarios. Metrics: total scenarios, pass rate, avg steps per scenario. Archive unused features. Update scenarios matching changed behavior. Audit report shared with team.", "Proactive feature file maintenance process."),
("What is BDD vs traditional test planning?", "Traditional: separate test plan document, often stale. BDD: scenarios in feature files, always current. Traditional: QA plans alone. BDD: whole team contributes. Traditional: traceability matrix. BDD: scenarios directly map to acceptance criteria. BDD eliminates duplicate documentation.", "Documentation efficiency comparison."),
("How does BDD support shift-left testing?", "Testing begins during requirements refinement with Three Amigos. Scenarios written before code — defects found in discussion, not production. Acceptance criteria validated early. Automation starts during development, not after. Reduces cost of defect fix by catching issues earlier.", "Shift-left concrete practices in BDD context."),
("What is BDD and DevOps integration?", "Feature files triggered in CI/CD pipeline. Tag-based suite selection per deployment stage. Smoke scenarios gate deployments. BDD reports published as deployment artifacts. Failed scenarios block promotion. Living documentation accessible to ops team for behavior reference.", "BDD as CI/CD quality gate."),
("What is conjunction in Gherkin (And/But)?", "And continues previous step type — And after Given is still precondition. But implies contrast/exception. Improves readability over repeating Given/When/Then. Rule: first step sets type, subsequent And/But follow. Never start scenario with And.", "Correct And/But usage rules."),
("How do you avoid technical jargon in Gherkin?", "Use business terms: \"submit order\" not \"click #submit-btn\". \"See confirmation\" not \"verify element .success-msg displayed\". If PO can't understand scenario, rewrite it. Technical details belong in step definitions. Review with PO in Three Amigos.", "Business-readable Gherkin validation with PO."),
("What is scenario discovery?", "Process of finding scenarios through conversation, not solo writing. Techniques: Example Mapping, Three Amigos, story mapping. Ask \"what could go wrong?\" for negative scenarios. Edge cases emerge from group discussion. Never automate scenarios discovered alone by QA.", "Collaborative scenario identification process."),
("What is BDD for microservices?", "Each service team owns feature files for its API behavior. Cross-service scenarios test integration flows. Contract scenarios verify service interfaces. Shared step library for common patterns (auth, pagination). Independent execution per service in CI.", "Microservice BDD organization model."),
("What is the BDD testing pyramid?", "Many API/service scenarios (fast, stable), fewer integration scenarios, minimal UI E2E scenarios. BDD applies at all levels — not just UI. Most Gherkin scenarios should be API-level for speed. UI scenarios for critical user journeys only.", "BDD applied across test pyramid layers."),
("How do you handle BDD training for developers?", "Developers write step definitions, not Gherkin. Train on: reading Gherkin, implementing step defs, Page Object pattern. Joint session with QA on Three Amigos. Developers attend first Three Amigos as observers. Gradually participate in scenario writing.", "Developer role clarity in BDD process."),
("What is BDD success criteria for a team?", "All new stories have Gherkin before development. Three Amigos happening regularly. PO reads and approves scenarios. Living documentation referenced in sprint reviews. Reduced requirement-related defects. Team members across roles contribute to feature files.", "Measurable team BDD adoption indicators."),
("What is BDD failure mode: QA-only Gherkin?", "QA writes feature files without PO or Dev input. Scenarios may not reflect business intent. Dev doesn't understand Gherkin. PO ignores feature files. Becomes traditional automation with Gherkin syntax — loses BDD collaboration value. Fix: mandatory Three Amigos.", "Recognize and fix QA-silo BDD anti-pattern."),
("What is BDD failure mode: 100% UI coverage?", "All scenarios test through UI — slow, brittle, expensive to maintain. BDD value is behavior specification, not UI testing. API and service-level scenarios are faster and more stable. Reserve UI scenarios for critical user journeys. Follow test pyramid.", "Test pyramid applied to BDD scenario distribution."),
("How do you write BDD scenarios for negative cases?", "Explicit negative scenario: \"Login with invalid password shows error\". Use Examples table for multiple invalid inputs. Tag @negative. One failure condition per scenario. Then step verifies specific error message. Don't combine multiple negative cases in one scenario.", "Negative scenario writing with clear assertions."),
("What is story mapping vs BDD?", "Story mapping: big-picture visualization of user journey across epics. BDD: detailed behavior examples for individual stories. Story mapping identifies WHAT to build. BDD specifies HOW it should behave. Complementary — story map feeds into Three Amigos scenarios.", "Complementary planning techniques."),
("How do you maintain ubiquitous language glossary?", "Shared document (Confluence/Wiki) listing business terms and definitions. Updated during Three Amigos when new terms emerge. Referenced when writing Gherkin. New team members read glossary during onboarding. Terms used identically in features, code, and discussions.", "Living glossary maintenance process."),
("What is BDD role of QA in Agile?", "QA facilitates Three Amigos, leads Gherkin writing, automates scenarios, maintains framework. QA shifts from \"test at end\" to \"specify behavior upfront\". QA ensures scenarios are testable and automatable. QA coaches PO and Dev on BDD practices.", "QA as BDD facilitator, not just automator."),
("How do you present BDD value to management?", "Show: reduced requirement defects (metrics), faster release confidence, living documentation reducing onboarding time, automated regression saving manual effort. Demo: PO reads Gherkin and confirms it matches intent. Calculate time saved vs manual regression.", "Business case for BDD investment."),
("What is Cucumber vs Behave vs SpecFlow?", "Cucumber-JVM: Java/Kotlin. Behave: Python. SpecFlow/Reqnroll: .NET. All use Gherkin syntax. Choose based on project tech stack. Concepts identical across implementations. Skills transfer between tools — Gherkin and BDD process are universal.", "Tool-agnostic BDD understanding."),
("What is periodic BDD retrospective?", "Monthly team retrospective on BDD practice: Are Three Amigos happening? Feature file quality? Scenario execution time? Flaky scenarios? Step definition maintainability? Action items for improvement. Continuous improvement of BDD process, not just tools.", "Continuous BDD process improvement mindset."),
("How do you handle conflicting scenarios in BDD?", "Two scenarios testing contradictory behavior indicates ambiguous requirements. Escalate to PO for clarification during Three Amigos. Don't automate until resolved. Document decision in scenario comment or linked Jira ticket. Conflicting scenarios signal communication gap.", "Conflict resolution through collaboration, not unilateral decision."),
]

