# Framework 50
fw = [
("How do you implement Page Object Model?", "Each web page is a Java class with locators as private fields and action methods. Constructor takes WebDriver. Methods represent user actions: login(String user, String pass). Tests/step defs call page methods, never access locators directly. BasePage class for common methods: click, type, wait.", "POM class structure with constructor injection of driver."),
("What is Page Factory pattern?", "PageFactory.initElements(driver, this) initializes @FindBy annotated elements lazily. @FindBy(id=\"email\") private WebElement email. Reduces boilerplate. Limitation: stale elements on dynamic pages. Prefer explicit waits in methods over @FindBy for AJAX-heavy applications.", "Page Factory with @FindBy and stale element caveat."),
("What is a hybrid automation framework?", "Combines Keyword-Driven (action keywords in Excel/JSON), Data-Driven (DataProvider/Excel), and Page Object Model. TestNG/Cucumber orchestrates. Keywords map to Java methods. Data externalized. POM handles UI. Maximizes reusability for teams with varied skill levels.", "How hybrid layers interact in practice."),
("What is DriverFactory pattern?", "Centralized WebDriver creation: getDriver() returns ThreadLocal driver. switch(browser) creates ChromeDriver, FirefoxDriver, etc. based on config. quitDriver() cleans up. Single point to change driver configuration. All tests use DriverFactory, never new ChromeDriver() directly.", "ThreadLocal DriverFactory implementation."),
("What is ConfigReader utility?", "Loads properties file based on environment: config-dev.properties, config-staging.properties. get(\"url\") returns property value. System property override: -Durl=... takes precedence. Singleton or static utility. Used by DriverFactory, API clients, DB connections throughout framework.", "Environment-aware config loading pattern."),
("How do you read Excel test data?", "Apache POI library reads .xlsx files. ExcelReader utility: getSheetData(String sheetName) returns Object[][]. DataProvider calls ExcelReader. Column headers map to test parameters. Keep test data in src/test/resources/testdata/. Separate data from code.", "POI-based Excel data provider integration."),
("How do you implement screenshot utility?", "ScreenshotUtil.capture(driver, name) saves PNG to target/screenshots/. Called from TestNG listener onTestFailure or Cucumber @After hook. Timestamp + test name in filename. Attach to ExtentReports/Allure. Create directory if not exists. Clean old screenshots periodically.", "Screenshot capture on failure integration."),
("What is a wait utility class?", "WaitUtil with methods: waitForVisible(locator), waitForClickable(locator), waitForText(locator, text). Centralizes WebDriverWait with configurable timeout from properties. FluentWait for polling interval customization. All page objects use WaitUtil instead of inline waits.", "Centralized explicit wait utility design."),
("What is a BaseTest class?", "Abstract class with @BeforeMethod/@AfterMethod for driver init/quit. @BeforeSuite for config loading. All test classes extend BaseTest. Provides getDriver(), config access. Listeners registered here or in testng.xml. Cucumber: hooks replace BaseTest lifecycle.", "BaseTest lifecycle for TestNG test classes."),
("What is a BasePage class?", "Parent class for all page objects. Common methods: click(WebElement), type(WebElement, text), isDisplayed(locator). Initialize WebDriverWait in constructor. All pages extend BasePage. Reduces duplication across page objects. Navigation methods: getTitle(), getCurrentUrl().", "Shared page object methods in base class."),
("How do you design API client wrapper?", "ApiClient class wraps REST Assured: get(endpoint), post(endpoint, body), put, delete. Handles auth header injection, base URI from config, common assertions. Service classes per resource: UserService extends ApiClient. Step definitions call service methods, not raw REST Assured.", "Service object pattern for API testing."),
("How do you implement database utility?", "DBUtil with getConnection(), query(sql, params), execute(sql, params), querySingle(). Uses JDBC with PreparedStatement for SQL injection prevention. Connection pool (HikariCP) for parallel tests. Read DB config from ConfigReader. Close connections in @AfterSuite.", "JDBC utility with connection pooling for parallel."),
("How do you structure Maven project for automation?", "src/test/java: tests, steps, pages, utils. src/test/resources: features, config, testdata. pom.xml: dependencies, surefire plugin, suite XML. testng.xml in resources/suites/. Separate modules for large projects: core, ui-tests, api-tests. .gitignore: target/, test-output/, screenshots/.", "Standard Maven automation project structure."),
("How do you implement logging in framework?", "Log4j2 or SLF4J with log4j2.xml configuration. Logger per class. Log test start/end, action steps, errors. Separate log file per test run. Thread name in log pattern for parallel debugging. Log level configurable via properties: DEBUG for dev, INFO for CI.", "Structured logging with parallel thread identification."),
("How do you integrate ExtentReports?", "ExtentManager singleton initializes ExtentReports in @BeforeSuite. Listener or hook creates ExtentTest per scenario. Log pass/fail with screenshots. flush() in @AfterSuite. SparkReporter for modern HTML dashboard. Configure report path, theme, system info in extent.properties.", "ExtentReports lifecycle with listener integration."),
("How do you integrate Allure reporting?", "allure-testng or allure-cucumber7-jvm dependency. @Step on page object methods. @Attachment for screenshots. allure.properties configures results directory. Generate: allure serve target/allure-results. Categories for failure classification. Trend history in Allure Docker Service.", "Allure setup with step-level reporting."),
("How do you design CI/CD pipeline for automation?", "Stages: Build → Smoke Test → Deploy Staging → Regression → Report. Parameterized: SUITE, ENV, BROWSER. Publish reports as artifacts. Slack/email on failure. Quality gate: smoke must pass for merge. Nightly full regression. Parallel agents for cross-browser.", "Complete CI/CD pipeline design for test automation."),
("How do you use Docker for test automation?", "Dockerfile: base image + Java + Maven + Chrome. docker-compose.yml: test app + selenium grid + test runner. Run: docker-compose up --abort-on-container-exit. Consistent environment across local and CI. Volume mount for reports. Pre-built images: selenium/standalone-chrome.", "Docker-based test execution environment."),
("How do you configure Selenium Grid?", "Hub-node architecture. hub:4444 receives tests, nodes execute. docker-compose for local grid. Capabilities: browserName, platform. testng.xml parallel tests connect to grid URL. Cloud alternative: BrowserStack/Sauce Labs. Monitor node capacity vs thread-count.", "Grid setup and capacity planning."),
("What is cloud browser testing?", "BrowserStack, Sauce Labs, LambdaTest provide managed browsers/devices. Capabilities builder sets browser/OS/version. RemoteWebDriver connects to cloud URL. Parallel cross-browser without local infrastructure. Cost per minute — optimize test efficiency. Integrate with CI via plugins.", "Cloud provider integration for cross-browser testing."),
("How do you manage test environments?", "Config properties per environment: dev, staging, prod-sanity. Jenkins parameter selects environment. Never run destructive tests on production. Environment health check in @BeforeSuite — skip if unavailable. Separate test accounts per environment. Document environment URLs and credentials policy.", "Multi-environment management without credential leaks."),
("How do you manage secrets in automation?", "Never commit passwords/API keys to git. Jenkins credentials store injects at runtime. Environment variables: System.getenv(\"API_KEY\"). Azure Key Vault / AWS Secrets Manager for enterprise. .gitignore secrets files. ConfigReader reads from env vars, not properties files, for sensitive data.", "Secrets management best practices."),
("What is test tagging strategy?", "Three tiers: @smoke (critical, every commit), @regression (full, nightly), @sanity (post-deploy). Module tags: @login, @checkout. Type tags: @ui, @api. Cross-cutting: @negative, @wip. Document tag definitions. CI jobs map to tag combinations.", "Hierarchical tag strategy with CI mapping."),
("How do you organize test suites?", "Separate testng.xml per suite: smoke.xml, regression.xml, api.xml. Each specifies groups/tags, parallel settings, listeners. CI job parameter selects suite. Smoke: 10-15 min. Regression: 1-2 hours. Sanity: 5 min post-deploy. Review suite composition monthly.", "Suite organization by execution frequency and scope."),
("How do you manage flaky tests?", "Track flakiness rate per test over 10 runs. Investigate: timing, data, environment. Fix root cause, don't just retry. Quarantine persistently flaky tests (@quarantine tag). Jira ticket for each flaky test. Target: less than 2% flaky rate. Retry as temporary measure only.", "Systematic flaky test management process."),
("What is framework maintenance strategy?", "Monthly: dependency updates, remove obsolete tests. Quarterly: refactor duplicated code, optimize slow tests. Version pin Selenium/TestNG. Automated dependency PRs with smoke validation. Code review for test code same as production code. Deprecation policy for old patterns.", "Long-term framework ownership plan."),
("What design patterns apply to automation?", "POM (Page Object), Factory (DriverFactory), Singleton (ConfigReader), Builder (TestDataBuilder), Strategy (BrowserStrategy), Facade (ApiClient), Observer (Listener). Don't over-engineer — use patterns where they reduce duplication. Match team's Java skill level.", "Appropriate pattern selection, not pattern overuse."),
("How do you implement Factory pattern for browsers?", "BrowserFactory.create(String browser) returns WebDriver. Switch on browser type: chrome, firefox, edge. Read headless, window size from config. Extensible: add new browser by adding case. DriverFactory delegates to BrowserFactory. Keeps driver creation logic centralized.", "BrowserFactory with config-driven browser selection."),
("How do you implement Builder pattern for test data?", "UserBuilder.newUser().withName(\"John\").withEmail(\"j@t.com\").withRole(\"admin\").build(). Fluent API for readable test data creation. Default values for optional fields. Used in @BeforeMethod or step definitions. Reduces test data boilerplate.", "Builder pattern for readable test data creation."),
("How do you implement Strategy pattern for browsers?", "BrowserStrategy interface: createDriver(), getCapabilities(). ChromeStrategy, FirefoxStrategy implementations. BrowserFactory selects strategy based on config. Enables adding browsers without modifying factory. Cleaner than switch-case for many browser types.", "Strategy pattern for extensible browser support."),
("How do you review automation code?", "Checklist: no static WebDriver, no Thread.sleep, locators not in tests, proper waits, data cleanup, meaningful assertions, no hardcoded values, proper exception handling. Same PR process as app code. Require 1 approval for test code PRs. Lint with Checkstyle/SpotBugs.", "Test code review standards and checklist."),
("How do you handle email verification in tests?", "MailHog or MailSlurp for test email capture. API retrieves email by recipient. Extract verification link/OTP from email body. Use in step definition to complete verification flow. Self-hosted MailHog in Docker for CI. Never use real email accounts in automation.", "Test email service integration pattern."),
("How do you validate PDF content in tests?", "Apache PDFBox library extracts text from downloaded PDF. Compare extracted text with expected content. Verify PDF downloaded successfully (file exists, size > 0). Use in @Then step for invoice/report validation. Store expected PDFs in test resources for comparison.", "PDF validation approach in test automation."),
("How do you implement custom annotations?", "Define @RequiresLogin, @CleanupData annotations. IAnnotationTransformer or IInvokedMethodListener processes them at runtime. @RequiresLogin triggers login in beforeInvocation. Self-documenting test requirements. Advanced pattern for framework governance.", "Custom annotation processing in TestNG listeners."),
("How do you version control automation framework?", "Git with feature branch workflow. testng.xml and feature files in repo. Config templates committed, secrets excluded. Tag releases: v1.0-smoke-suite. CHANGELOG for framework changes. Semantic versioning for shared libraries. Branch protection on main.", "Git workflow for test automation codebase."),
("How do you handle property file management?", "config.properties for defaults. config-{env}.properties for environment overrides. Maven resource filtering for CI values. ConfigReader merges: system props > env props > default props. Never duplicate keys across files. Document all properties in README.", "Property precedence and environment override pattern."),
("How do you implement reporting aggregation?", "Merge TestNG XML + Cucumber JSON into unified dashboard. Jenkins aggregates across parallel jobs. Custom script parses both formats into single HTML. Track pass rate, duration, flaky count trends. Grafana dashboard for historical metrics.", "Multi-format report aggregation strategy."),
("How do you classify test failures?", "Categories: AUT (application bug), TEST (automation bug), ENV (environment issue), DATA (test data problem). Listener classifies based on exception type and context. Report shows category breakdown. Helps prioritize fixes: AUT → Jira bug, TEST → fix automation.", "Failure classification taxonomy for triage."),
("How do you build test metrics dashboard?", "Track: pass rate, execution time, flaky rate, scenario count, failure categories. Source: TestNG XML, Cucumber JSON, CI build data. Grafana or custom HTML dashboard. Weekly email summary to team. Trend over 30/90 days. Alert on pass rate drop below threshold.", "Metrics-driven quality visibility."),
("How do you handle multi-module Maven projects?", "Parent pom.xml with dependencyManagement. Modules: automation-core (utils, pages), ui-tests, api-tests. Each module has own testng.xml. CI runs modules in parallel or sequence. Shared dependencies managed in parent. Reusable core module published as internal artifact.", "Multi-module structure for large automation projects."),
("What is framework versioning strategy?", "Semantic versioning: MAJOR (breaking changes), MINOR (new features), PATCH (fixes). Pin framework version in consumer projects. Release notes for each version. Deprecation warnings before removing features. Backward compatibility for step definitions and config.", "Version management for shared automation libraries."),
("How do you implement action class (Actions API)?", "ActionsUtil wraps Selenium Actions class: dragAndDrop, hover, doubleClick, rightClick, key combinations. Methods take WebElement parameters. Used by page objects for complex interactions. Centralized action logic with proper wait before action.", "Actions API wrapper for complex UI interactions."),
("How do you handle YAML configuration?", "SnakeYAML library parses .yml config files. Nested structure for complex config: environments > staging > url. More readable than properties for hierarchical config. ConfigReader supports both YAML and properties. Choose based on config complexity.", "YAML vs properties for complex configuration."),
("How do you implement test data builder?", "TestDataBuilder creates complex test objects fluently. UserBuilder, OrderBuilder with sensible defaults. Reduces test setup code. Integrates with @BeforeMethod and step definitions. Faker library for random realistic data. Builder output used in API setup and UI verification.", "Fluent builder for complex test data setup."),
("How do you implement Facade for API testing?", "ApiFacade provides simplified interface: createUserAndLogin() handles registration, login, token storage in one call. Hides multi-step API interactions from step definitions. Step def calls facade, facade orchestrates service calls. Reduces step definition complexity.", "Facade simplifying multi-step API interactions."),
("How do you handle file download verification?", "ChromeOptions: setDownloadPath to known directory. After click download, WaitUtil waits for file to appear. Verify filename and size. Clean download directory in @AfterMethod. Remote grid: enable download in node config. Assert file content if needed.", "Download verification with wait for file existence."),
("How do you implement listener framework?", "ListenerFactory registers listeners based on config: screenshot listener, logging listener, report listener. Enabled/disabled via properties. BaseListener abstract class with common logic. Register in testng.xml or @Listeners. Extensible: add new listener without changing existing code.", "Pluggable listener architecture design."),
("How do you handle window/tab switching?", "WindowHelper utility: getCurrentHandle(), switchToWindow(handle), closeCurrentSwitchToMain(). Wait for new window after click. Used in page objects for popup handling. Step definitions call page object methods. Always return to main window in finally block.", "Multi-window handling utility pattern."),
("How do you implement retry in framework?", "IRetryAnalyzer with max 2 retries. IAnnotationTransformer applies globally. Retry only on specific exceptions: TimeoutException, StaleElementReferenceException. Log retry count in listener. Report shows retry attempts. Quarantine test if retry rate exceeds 30%.", "Smart retry with exception filtering and quarantine."),
("How do you onboard new team members to framework?", "Day 1: README, project structure walkthrough. Day 2: Run existing tests, read feature files. Day 3: Write simple scenario with pair programming. Day 4: Implement step definitions. Day 5: Solo task with code review. Documentation: architecture diagram, coding standards, common patterns.", "Structured onboarding plan for automation framework."),
]

