# Scenario 50
sc = [
("How do you investigate flaky tests?", "Check last 10 runs: pass/fail pattern. Reproduce locally 20 times. Add logging around failure point. Common causes: timing, shared data, environment diff. Fix root cause. Temporary: retry with limit. Track in flaky test register. Target fix within 1 sprint.", "Systematic root cause analysis, not blind retry."),
("How do you debug parallel test failures?", "Run with thread-count=1 to confirm sequential pass. Add thread name to logs. Check ThreadLocal driver implementation. Look for static shared state. Verify unique test data per thread. Run 2 threads locally, then scale. Common fix: ThreadLocal + unique data.", "Parallel-specific debugging methodology."),
("How do you analyze CI-only failures?", "Compare: browser version, OS, screen size, timing, env config. Run CI Docker image locally. Enable verbose logging in CI. Capture artifacts: screenshots, logs, HAR. Check if parallel in CI but sequential locally. Increase wait timeouts as temporary diagnostic.", "Local vs CI environment comparison approach."),
("How do you handle test timeout issues?", "Identify slow step via timeline report. Root cause: excessive waits, slow API, heavy page. Fix: optimize waits, mock slow services, API setup instead of UI. Set realistic timeOut on @Test. Never just increase timeout without investigation.", "Root cause fix, not timeout inflation."),
("How do you fix StaleElementReferenceException?", "Element changed in DOM after find. Fix: re-find element before interaction. Use explicit wait with fresh lookup. Page Object method re-locates element each call. Avoid storing WebElement as instance variable on dynamic pages. ExpectedConditions.refreshed() for re-fetch.", "Re-find element pattern for dynamic pages."),
("How do you handle session expired mid-test?", "Detect login page redirect in @BeforeStep or page object guard method. Re-authenticate via API (fast) and continue. Or fail with clear message: \"Session expired\". Prevention: refresh token in long-running tests. Set appropriate session timeout in test environment.", "Session recovery or clear failure strategy."),
("How do you fix reports not generating in CI?", "Check report output path exists and is writable. Verify listener registered in testng.xml. Ensure @AfterSuite flush() runs even on failure (alwaysRun=true). Check CI archives correct directory. Plugin paths relative to working directory. Permissions on CI agent.", "CI-specific report path and permission debugging."),
("How do you fix screenshots not captured on failure?", "Verify listener @AfterMethod runs on failure (alwaysRun=true). Check driver not null and not quit before screenshot. RemoteWebDriver: screenshot capability enabled. Path writable in CI. Cucumber: @After hook checks scenario.isFailed(). Debug: log in listener to confirm invocation.", "Listener execution order and driver state debugging."),
("How do you handle DB connection pool exhaustion?", "Limit parallel thread-count to match pool size. HikariCP: maxPoolSize = thread-count + 2. Close connections in @AfterMethod/@AfterSuite. Don't create connection per query — reuse pool. Monitor pool metrics. Separate read-only pool for validation queries.", "Connection pool sizing for parallel tests."),
("How do you fix test data collision in parallel?", "Unique data per thread: UUID suffix on emails, usernames. Separate DB schema per thread (advanced). API creates fresh data in @BeforeMethod. Never use hardcoded shared accounts. Cleanup in @AfterMethod. Data isolation is mandatory for parallel reliability.", "Unique test data generation per parallel thread."),
("How do you handle browser version mismatch?", "WebDriverManager auto-matches driver to browser. Pin browser version in CI Docker image. Grid: specify browser version in capabilities. Cloud: set version in capabilities. Document supported browser versions. CI matrix tests specific versions.", "Browser/driver version alignment strategy."),
("How do you fix headless vs headed test differences?", "Headless may render differently: set window size explicitly. Disable headless for debugging, enable for CI. ChromeOptions: --window-size=1920,1080. Some features (PDF viewer, downloads) behave differently headless. Test critical flows in both modes.", "Headless configuration for consistent rendering."),
("How do you handle SSL certificate errors in CI?", "ChromeOptions: --ignore-certificate-errors for test environments only. Never in production tests. Import cert to truststore for proper fix. Custom TrustManager for REST Assured API tests. Document which environments have self-signed certs.", "Test environment SSL handling, not production bypass."),
("How do you configure proxy in Selenium Grid?", "Proxy capability in DesiredCapabilities. HTTP proxy for corporate networks. Grid node proxy settings in node config. REST Assured: RestAssured.proxy(). Test proxy connectivity in @BeforeSuite. Document proxy requirements for team.", "Proxy configuration for corporate CI environments."),
("How do you verify file downloads in automation?", "Set download directory via browser preferences. Wait for file existence with polling. Verify filename pattern and file size. Parse content (CSV, PDF, Excel). Clean download folder in @AfterMethod. Grid: configure download path on node.", "Reliable download verification pattern."),
("How do you handle file upload in headless mode?", "sendKeys with absolute file path to hidden input element. Works in headless. File must exist on CI agent. Store test files in src/test/resources/. Remote grid: LocalFileDetector. Never use Robot class for file dialog.", "sendKeys upload approach for headless CI."),
("How do you handle iFrame testing failures?", "Switch to frame before interaction: driver.switchTo().frame(locator). Interact with elements inside frame. switchTo().defaultContent() after. Nested frames: switchTo().parentFrame(). Wait for frame availability. Encapsulate in page object methods.", "Frame switching with proper context cleanup."),
("How do you handle JavaScript alert dialogs?", "Alert alert = wait.until(ExpectedConditions.alertIsPresent()). alert.accept() or dismiss(). Verify alert text before accepting. Handle unexpected alerts in @AfterStep to prevent next step failure. Don't use Robot for alerts.", "ExpectedConditions.alertIsPresent() pattern."),
("How do you handle cookie domain issues?", "Delete all cookies in @BeforeMethod for clean state. Set cookies via Selenium for auth bypass. Verify cookie domain matches application domain. Cross-subdomain tests: set domain explicitly. API-set cookies may differ from Selenium-set — test both paths.", "Cookie management for test isolation."),
("How do you handle multi-window test failures?", "Store main window handle before opening popup. Switch to new window by iterating handles. Perform actions in popup. Close popup, switch back to main. Wait for new window with WebDriverWait. WindowHelper utility encapsulates logic.", "Window handle management pattern."),
("How do you fix AJAX wait failures?", "Never use Thread.sleep for AJAX. Explicit wait: ExpectedConditions.invisibilityOfElementLocated(loader) or visibilityOfElementLocated(content). Wait for specific AJAX indicator disappearance. FluentWait with polling. Set reasonable timeout (15-30s) in config.", "AJAX-specific wait conditions."),
("How do you handle test environment unavailable?", "@BeforeSuite health check: ping API, verify DB connection. SkipException if environment down. CI: retry environment provisioning. Alert team via Slack. Don't waste 30 min running tests against dead environment. Log clear message: \"Staging unavailable\".", "Environment health check before suite execution."),
("How do you test feature flags?", "API or DB sets feature flag state in @BeforeMethod. Test both enabled and disabled scenarios with tags: @flag-on, @flag-off. Reset flag in @AfterMethod. Coordinate with dev team on flag names. Don't test both states in same scenario.", "Feature flag setup/teardown per scenario."),
("How do you handle OTP in automation?", "Test environment: disable OTP or use fixed test OTP (123456). API bypass: generate OTP via test API endpoint. MailHog captures OTP email, extract code. Never automate real SMS OTP. Document OTP bypass approach for test environment.", "Test environment OTP bypass strategy."),
("How do you handle CAPTCHA in automation?", "Disable CAPTCHA in test environment (recommended). Test API bypass endpoint. Use test-only CAPTCHA key that always passes. Never use CAPTCHA solving services in CI. If CAPTCHA mandatory, test up to CAPTCHA step and verify it appears.", "CAPTCHA disable/bypass in test environments."),
("How do you verify email in automation?", "MailHog/MailSlurp captures test emails. API query: get latest email for recipient. Assert subject, body content, links. Extract verification URL and navigate. Self-hosted MailHog in Docker Compose with test app.", "Email testing with mail capture service."),
("How do you test OAuth flows?", "Test OAuth provider mock or sandbox. Automate authorization flow in dedicated scenarios. API shortcut: obtain token directly for non-OAuth scenarios. Store client ID/secret in CI credentials. Scope OAuth tests with @oauth tag.", "OAuth test strategy with mock/sandbox provider."),
("How do you handle JWT token refresh in tests?", "API login obtains JWT in @BeforeMethod. Store in ThreadLocal or context. Refresh token before expiry in long scenarios. Inject as Authorization header for API steps. Cookie/localStorage for UI tests. Handle 401 by re-authenticating.", "Token lifecycle management in test suite."),
("How do you test rate limiting?", "Verify 429 status code after exceeding limit. Use dedicated rate-limit test account. Reset rate limit via test API or wait. Tag @rate-limit for isolated execution. Don't run rate limit tests in shared regression — affects other tests.", "Isolated rate limit testing approach."),
("How do you optimize test execution time?", "API setup instead of UI login. Headless browser. Parallel execution. Remove redundant @BeforeMethod steps. Cache static test data. Skip non-critical scenarios in smoke. Profile with timeline report. Target: smoke 10 min, regression 1 hour.", "Data-driven optimization priorities."),
("How do you test payment gateway integration?", "Use sandbox/test mode API keys. Test card numbers provided by gateway (4111111111111111). Verify success, decline, and error flows. Never use real cards. Mock gateway for unit tests, sandbox for E2E. Tag @payment for isolated execution.", "Payment sandbox testing with test cards."),
("How do you handle WebSocket testing?", "Java WebSocket client connects to test endpoint. Send/receive messages programmatically. Verify message content and order. UI test: verify WebSocket-driven UI updates with explicit wait. Close connection in @AfterMethod.", "WebSocket client testing approach."),
("How do you test GraphQL APIs?", "HTTP POST with query in body. REST Assured or HttpClient. Verify response data path. Test error cases: invalid query, missing variables. Schema validation against GraphQL schema. Tag @graphql scenarios separately.", "GraphQL query testing in automation."),
("How do you test responsive design?", "Set window sizes: 1920x1080 (desktop), 768x1024 (tablet), 375x667 (mobile). Verify element visibility/layout at each size. Chrome DevTools mobile emulation. Cloud services for real device testing. Tag @responsive for separate execution.", "Viewport-based responsive testing."),
("How do you integrate performance testing?", "Separate performance suite with JMeter/Gatling. Functional tests verify correctness, performance tests verify speed. Don't mix load testing with functional regression. Baseline response time assertions in API tests. Alert on response time degradation trend.", "Separation of functional and performance testing."),
("How do you test in production safely?", "Read-only sanity tests only: homepage loads, API health check. No create/update/delete operations. Dedicated prod-sanity testng.xml. Run post-deployment only. @prod tag with strict CI restriction. Monitor test impact on production metrics.", "Safe production sanity testing guardrails."),
("How do you verify deployment with automation?", "Post-deploy sanity suite: 5-10 critical scenarios. Run against newly deployed environment. Gate: deployment rolls back if sanity fails. Smoke within 5 minutes of deploy. Results notify deployment team. Separate from full regression.", "Post-deployment verification gate process."),
("How do you test rollback scenarios?", "Deploy new version, run sanity. Simulate rollback to previous version. Re-run sanity against rolled-back version. Verify data integrity after rollback. Requires automated deployment pipeline. Tag @rollback for manual/scheduled execution.", "Rollback verification test process."),
("How do you test blue-green deployment?", "Run regression against green environment before switch. Post-switch sanity on green. Keep blue tests ready for rollback verification. DNS/load balancer switch automated. Test both environments during transition period.", "Dual-environment deployment testing."),
("How do you test canary releases?", "Run smoke against canary instance with 5% traffic. Compare metrics: error rate, response time vs stable. Automated canary analysis (ACA) in CI. Rollback canary if metrics degrade. Functional tests target canary URL specifically.", "Canary validation with metric comparison."),
("How do you handle localization testing?", "Set browser locale/language preferences. Verify UI text in expected language. Test date/number formatting per locale. Data-driven: Examples table with locale and expected text. Tag @i18n for separate execution. Store translations in test data files.", "Locale-specific UI verification approach."),
("How do you integrate accessibility testing?", "Axe-core library integrated with Selenium. Run accessibility scan after page load. Assert zero critical violations. Tag @a11y scenarios. Report WCAG violations with element details. Run in CI but not blocking initially — trend toward zero violations.", "Automated accessibility scanning integration."),
("How do you test third-party widgets?", "Mock third-party in test environment where possible. If real widget required: wait for widget load indicator. Test integration points, not widget internals. Isolate widget failures with @third-party tag. Fallback: verify placeholder when widget unavailable.", "Third-party widget test isolation strategy."),
("How do you handle chart/graph verification?", "Extract chart data via JavaScript executor: return chart data from canvas/SVG. Compare data values programmatically. Visual regression for chart appearance (optional). Don't rely on pixel comparison — validate underlying data.", "Data-level chart validation over visual comparison."),
("How do you test Excel export validation?", "Download file, read with Apache POI. Verify row count, column headers, cell values. Compare with expected test data. Clean up downloaded files. Handle large exports with streaming reader.", "POI-based export content verification."),
("How do you handle network HAR capture for debugging?", "BrowserMob Proxy or Selenium 4 devtools for HAR capture. Save HAR on test failure. Analyze failed requests, response codes, timing. Attach HAR to bug reports. Enable only on failure to avoid performance impact.", "Network-level debugging on failure."),
("How do you coordinate load and functional testing?", "Never run load tests against shared test environment with functional tests. Separate environments: func-test, load-test. Schedule load tests off-hours. Functional tests verify features; load tests verify scalability. Different tools, different environments, different schedules.", "Environment separation for load vs functional tests."),
("How do you handle mobile web testing?", "Chrome mobile emulation with device metrics. Cloud services (BrowserStack) for real devices. Responsive design testing at mobile viewports. Touch action simulation via Actions class. Separate @mobile tag suite. Appium for native apps — different framework.", "Mobile web vs native app testing distinction."),
("How do you manage test execution reporting failures?", "Verify report plugin paths are writable. Check listener registration. @AfterSuite flush with alwaysRun=true. CI archives correct output directory. Fallback: generate report programmatically in IReporter. Log report generation status.", "Report generation failure troubleshooting."),
("How do you handle A/B test automation?", "API sets user bucket before test. Verify A variant experience for bucket A user. Separate scenarios for each variant. Reset bucket in @AfterMethod. Coordinate with product team on experiment flags. Tag @ab-test for isolated execution.", "A/B test bucket assignment in automation."),
]

